The paper discusses algorithmic information theory, which is a subfield of theoretical computer science and mathematical logic. The paper covers topics such as Kolmogorov complexity, randomness, and effective Hausdorff dimension, which are related to information theory, computational complexity, and computability theory. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.IT (Information Theory). Other likely sub-categories include cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
